The following script possibly reproduces the same issue without extui:
```lua
local api = vim.api
vim.cmd.tabnew()
local buf1 = api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)
api.nvim_open_win(buf1, false, { split = 'right' })
api.nvim_create_autocmd('WinClosed', {
  callback = function()
    api.nvim_buf_delete(buf1, { force = true })
    local buf2 = api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)
    local opts = { relative = 'editor', row = 5, col = 5, width = 5, height = 5 }
    api.nvim_open_win(buf2, false, opts)
  end
})
vim.schedule(function()
  vim.cmd('quit')
end)
```

Perhaps the following check in `win_close_othertab()` is needed in `win_close()` as well:
```c
  // Autocommands may again cause closing this window to leave only floats.
  // Check again; we'll not bother closing floating windows this time.
  if (tp->tp_lastwin->w_floating && one_window(win, tp)) {
    emsg(e_floatonly);
    goto leave_open;
  }
```
Minimal fix (does not report E5601):
```diff
diff --git a/src/nvim/window.c b/src/nvim/window.c
index 276b2a44b4..0e91c48367 100644
--- a/src/nvim/window.c
+++ b/src/nvim/window.c
@@ -2842,6 +2842,7 @@ int win_close(win_T *win, bool free_buf, bool force)
   // Autocommands may have closed the window already, or closed the only
   // other window or moved to another tab page.
   if (!win_valid(win) || (!win->w_floating && last_window(win))
+      || (lastwin->w_floating && one_window(win, NULL))
       || close_last_window_tabpage(win, free_buf, prev_curtab)) {
     return FAIL;
   }
```
I'm not sure whether E5601 should be reported in this case, because neither E444 nor E5601 is reported when there are no other tabpages (when the `!win->w_floating && last_window(win)` condition is satisfied).

Hmm, indeed NULL buffer is still a problem.

So I guess it needs this as well:
```c
    if (win->w_buffer == NULL) {
      // If the buffer was removed from the window we have to give it any buffer.
      win->w_buffer = firstbuf;
      firstbuf->b_nwindows++;
      win_init_empty(win);
    } else if (did_decrement && win->w_buffer == bufref.br_buf && bufref_valid(&bufref)) {
      // close_buffer decremented the window count, but we're keeping the window.
      // As the window is still viewing the buffer, increment the count.
      win->w_buffer->b_nwindows++;
    }
```
